    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-19T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-19T21:00:00-05:00" n="289"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/15150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-20T09:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 20, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1982. Embassy’s despatch 1580, September 16.<note n="71" xml:id="d289fn71">Not
                        printed.</note> Telegram of October 15 from Clubb at Tihwa states native
                    disturbances reported in Altai region and south Sinkiang and Turki language
                    circulars said recently <pb facs="0373" n="363" xml:id="pg_363"/> distributed in
                    Tihwa calling on people to rise against Sheng’s rule.</p>
                <p>Clubb reports (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) that Chinese officials reputedly believe
                    disturbances are instigated by Soviets, but he believes unsettled political
                    grievances of non-Chinese population and continuing economic deterioration are
                    important factors in this situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
